Package uk.ac.ncl.csc8002.coursework.part1.car

Class CarFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ncl.csc8002.coursework.part1.car.CarFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Car
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LargeCar, SmallCar

    public abstract class CarFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements Car
    A car factory is a class which implements common behaviour among all car types and provides static methods to return instances of different car types. The class implements the Car interface, implementing all but one method.
    Author:
    Andrew Brown

      • addFuel

        public int addFuel​(int fuelAdded)
        Method from car interface to add fuel to the car's fuel tank. The level of used fuel is checked and is compared with the amount of fuel added, if the fuel added is greater than the required fuel then only the required fuel is added. If the amount of fuel added is less than the required fuel then that amount is added in full.
        Specified by:
        addFuel in interface Car
        Parameters:
        fuelAdded - the amount of whole liters of fuel to add to the fuel tank
        Returns:
        the whole litre value of fuel actually added to the fuel tank
